So our last panel is here
to talk about marine life.

00:00:13.150 --> 00:00:15.440
I don't know if
anybody ever thought

00:00:15.440 --> 00:00:17.640
that the supply of
marine life in the ocean

00:00:17.640 --> 00:00:22.310
was inexhaustible or not
subject to the stresses

00:00:22.310 --> 00:00:23.570
that humans can put on it.

00:00:23.570 --> 00:00:29.030
But if not, by now we probably
are keenly aware of this issue.

00:00:29.030 --> 00:00:31.140
And it only gets more keen.

00:00:31.140 --> 00:00:33.060
So this panel will
talk about that.

00:00:33.060 --> 00:00:35.780
And here to moderate
is John Mandelman,

00:00:35.780 --> 00:00:41.570
who is the vice president of the
Anderson Cabot Center for Ocean

00:00:41.570 --> 00:00:45.232
Life and the chief scientist
at the New England Aquarium.

